caption: Original hamburg set is really good! Salad that comes with also crunchy and perfect.

Literally a their food is amazing. I would recommend the curry cutlet and the chili Tokyo Hamburg but it’s all SO good.
DELICIOUS!!! We got these triangle seaweed snacks :)
Very tasty. This reminded me of what I would find at a restaurant in Japan. The katsu and curry are both especially good. Credit cards are now accepted, which makes eating here easier.
Delicious food, clean establishment, wonderful service. I will be back with more friends.
Loved the kicking chicken (spicy ginger fried) dish.
delicious yaki dons
I had an amazing time at this restaurant. We liked the first-rate vibes and the meals. The waiters are super affable. I am glad we eventually decided to try this place.
This place provides great service and delicious meals. The best restaurant around town. The meals arrived fast and the rates were economical. Recommended.

Charming little Japanese eatery with plenty of options. Came here at least once a week while commuting in winter for a warm bowl of miso and a full plate of hamburger curry. Kept me full and warm all the way home.
Very friendly, food was done on time, curry was good. A little more expensive than I expected.
Great traditional Japanese food priced well

Excellent Japanese curry here. We got takeout and I was very pleased by how they had packed it. The katsu was somehow even still crispy. Definitely get the pickles, egg and cheese. They give a large amount of food for the price. This place is cash only but there's an ATM in the building.
Amazing customer service and DELICIOUS food. Miss the atmosphere but still glad I can support doing takeout.
Chicken katsu curry go to in Cambridge.
Rivals the curry I had in Japan.  I am so glad I found this place.
Food is fantastic.

I live pretty far from here, but come here regularly. We always get the Tokyo Hamburg set and yaki beef tofu.... but everything is good.  Recently saw a friend who used to live here.... he said that this was one of the three places he has to go when he comes back to town.
Love this place
Love this place

Cheap and delicious. Known primarily for its hamburger-and-rice sets but also has multiple pescetarian-friendly options. I've been coming here for many years and plan to do so until I move away from Massachusetts -- this is the best comfort food money can buy in the Lesley University complex.

This is a small place with not much seating. However it's totally worth! Not only is the food delicious but also the service is fast. It is cash only! I appreciate that the menu is not very large. However I don't think there are vegan options; there are vegetarian and pescatarian options.
Cafe Mami's Wafu Burger is the best.

Tasty gyudon, it is almost similar with that I had in Korea. Update: I visited again and tried cutlet Don and cutlet set with tonkatsu sauce. Cutlet Don is fine, nothing special. Cutlet is good but tonkatsu sauce is a bit sour. And the salad sauce was the worst. I think the conventional sauce from the starmarket is much better.
Had a awesome experience in this place with my kid. The food arrived quick and the service is just great. Prices are fair.
Average Japanese home cooking. Their curries could use a bit more veg. Their fried stuff is quite good though. Don't forget to bring cash.
Great food for a reasonable price. The wait time is also not too long. Would HIGHLY recommend for anyone who wants to eat a nice, decent Japanese food.
This restaurant has been one of my favorite places in years. All their dishes taste superb.

The food taste wasnt bad but not as good as people scream.  The experience for me was not acceptable ,  i was paying cash and do admit i was short on tip ( not quite 15%)  but before i could go to atm the waitress was already telling me i didnt give 15% and was telling me to pay more( not asking , but telling). Went there with 1 other person during Thursday around 12:15 for lunch. They have 4 small (2seaters) tables and 4 seats by kitchen bar. We were seated right away but had to share the table with other 2. We ordered Pork cutlet curry set that comes with salad and miso mist soup. Food came out in 10 minutes or so and all are above average. Food wise I can give 5 stars but eating area is just too small. Their service is really fast. I would visit again.
Good food at Porter Square. It was kinda difficult to find though within the building.
This curry is some of the best comfort food I've ever had.
I've been coming here for tatsuta curry for nearly 10 years now. Consistently excellent food with large portions for a fair price. Sometimes a wait but always worth it.
The curry is aaammmaaaazzziiiinnnngg!!!! Best Curry in Boston ever!
One of my Favorite restaurants in the Porter Square location among all the other Japanese restaurants. All of the restaurants are very good, so you can never go wrong!

Horrible experience. The food was expensive, bad, not authentic in the least, and both the fried chicken and hamburger tasted of old burnt oil. We ordered two “Japanese” curries, one of the plate had a huge amount of curry sauce, whilst the other plate had almost none at all. As this was part of a “set”, we also got instant miso soup (the one with hot water and powder), and a salad that looked like it was cut up and prepared 5 hours before we got it. Oh, and we got two plastic glasses with lukewarm tap water. As other reviews have noted, the place was also full of fruit flies which was pretty disgusting.  To finish the bad experience of, right when we were about to leave the Thai waitress shouted at us and tried shaming us in front of the other customers because we only left 10% tip. She said that she wanted at least 15%. Who in their right mind would have the nerve of doing that? Especially considering the unsanitary restaurant and disproportionate food that taste of burnt oil and grease.

Great food for a fair price! $10 pork cutlet curry with a miso soup and salad. The restaurant is small but the waiter was very accommodating, moving a table to allow our party of 4 to sit in a space meant for 3. Definitely would come back again!
One of the better places in Boston for Katsu Curry! Their Gyu-don is good too.
Consistently one of my favorite places to eat in all of the Greater Boston area.  Food is delicious every time and the staff is very kind.  Highly recommend.
Overall great experience!  Food was delicious 👌

Under the radar amazing restaurant!!! If you go on an off-peak time, there will be no wait. Fast service, consistent food, and great price. The best yaki don (with an egg) I've ever had, as well as the chicken katsu curry. The secret sauce - can't get enough. Thank you!

Food was great! The line was long, but the wait was short.  We were set very close to the chief.  There was only one waitress, but she worked very hard to make sure everyone got the needed attention.  I got the curry, but we wanted to try everything on the menu!
Food is great! Pretty close to authentic (only place better I know is Ittoku). Seating is limited, tho.
Really nice comfort food at affordable prices

Fantastic food at reasonable prices. Do note, Cash Only.

Hidden gem inside a university food court. It's cash only but the food is delicious and affordable and the portions are decent. You also get unlimited rice refills if you like rice. The service is fast. During prime time there might be a wait but since the turnover is quick fast the wait is usually under 30 mins
This is my favorite Japanese place! I always order the spicy beef rice bowl and crave it in between visits. Yummy!

This place may be small. But the food is great and the portion is huge. This a cash only bussiness.  There is alot of choices to pick from too. From veg lover to just 100 meat. The curry is amazing too.

nice little hole in the wall place with decent portion. my only complaint is that it is cash only but the whole food court area is. there is  bank of america atm around the corner but in today's society credit cards should be accepted everywhere!
Ive been coming here for over 15 years. The food, the service, and the prices are always great. It's definitely worth trying if you haven't.

CASH ONLY. Cafe Mami is great place, with delicious food and very fair prices. They always make the food the way I like and very accommodating. I usually go once a week.

Best place to eat at the complex.  Definitely something new to try when you want other japanese cuisine other than ramen or sushi.  Waiting time is much less than other places on the same floor.  I recommend trying the hamburg sets with sauce.  Just like all the other restaurants in the complex, Cafe Mami is cash only.  #JapaneseFood #Porter #Hamburg

Delicious little authentic Japanese cafe. Only a few minutes away from the Porter T stop. Pricesery reasonable, and everything tastes homemade. Very limited seating, but the tables turn around relatively quickly, and you can order takeaway, too. A great stop whenever you're in the area and need a meal.
It's a great, quick, small Japanese restaurant. Has great curry and don.
Funny food, decent service.
CASH ONLY establishment. They have a break between 4:00pm - 5:00pm daily so don't come during that time!

**Note: CASH ONLY**  This place is absolutely fantastic. When I get a craving for home style Japanese food I come here to get my fix!  This place has pretty limited seating so during the mealtime rush be prepared to wait and/or eat and leave!  (2 tables that can sit about 4-6 each with 3 seats facing the kitchen)  It's located within Lesley University (which contains a food court).  Now if you have trouble finding a parking space there's a parking lot in the back of the university (turn onto Roseland street.  if you come on a Sunday the rate is really affordable though for normal weekday hours I'm not too sure.  This place has a little bit of everything in regards to homestyle japanese cooking.  I tend to get the hamburg steak since I really enjoy the savory flavors that it provides (there's an assortment of different types of sauces but teriyaki is my favorite).  The curries are also quite tasty (do note that they differ from Indian curries).  Also if you love green tea, their milkeshake is also fantastic (everyone I get to try it loves it!).  The place is cash only but there's a bank of america ATM right next to it (by the security desk) so fear not!
I thought the food was ok but the staff was really nice and friendly
Pretty good Japanese food, especially the curry and Oyaki don. Huge portions too! Note that there is pretty limited seating though so you might have to wait, especially with a larger party.
Price is fair, fairly fast and food is delicious

Top notch Japanese curry - have been here over ten times and never regret eating here. i always get the hamburg curry with a fried egg and cheese, and their green tea milkshakes are quite delightful :)

I always get the yaki donburi rice bowl here. It comes with thinly sliced strips of beef over a bed of rice. The spicy mayo sauce paired with the beef is mouthwatering. It is a small shop so there is limited seating but if you get a seat, it is well worth every minute.
Pork and curry was awesome,highly recommend.
Good food, cheap price, but limited seating

The service here needs serious improvement.  The chubby Thai waitress was asking multiple different parties for extra tip tonight and rushing them out.  Never have I seen a waitress be so rude and disrespectful panhandling for an extra dollar.  I thought maybe they were rude to her so she was returning the favor but when it came to our bill she did the same.  She asked for one extra dollar and started yelling in Thai.  Really hope the owner gets it together and hires better workers.
Good variety of japanese food and easy to park your car.
Great active place with a lot of people and good atmosphere

I come here often for lunch mostly takeout and couldn’t be happier. Food, service, and price are awesome. Why people would go to Panera’s where there are such awesome food choices like this is beyond me!

It isn't exactly appetizing to see six fruit flies sitting on the wall next to your head and to have to constantly swat them away from your food. Maybe I'll come back again in the winter....
Great food, friendly staff. Our go to place for Japanese dinner. All the dishes I've tried were great!

Cafe Mami is a hidden jewel , always consistent with quality and delicious dishes, I have tried them all, there is not one that I did not like, highly recommend.

Came here again after 2 years. Still very good. Enjoy the hamburger steak. Definitely worth a visit if you're in the area.

I heard so many good things about cafe Mami and I was happy that I finally get to try it. This place is cash only so make sure to go to the ATM ahead of time. The place is also very small that only fits about 12 people. The price are pretty reasonable and the portions are huge. I would definitely come back again.

One of the first places your will see is Cafe Mami and it will usually have a line so be prepared to wait. they don't have many tables but it move relatively quickly. My favorite are the Japanese style burger patties.  On you way out to can also stop by the asian food markets and if you are anything like me fail horribly at trying to make something just as delicious. I love their fried chicken curry
Porter Square Exchange mall with its small avenue of Japanese eateries is a must visit if you have the time. Cafe Mami leads the list
Came here for lunch and ordered both the Yaki Don (served over rice) and Pork Cutlet Curry - delicious! Cheap prices but great quality and portions. Will definitely come back to try the other dishes.
The lunch specials are good and cheap. Location is in a mall, but teh actual space is cozy enough.
Best Oyaki Don I had in Boston. I order it literally every time. My bf loves their Curry Chicken Cutlet rice. Remember to take out a Green Tea Milk Shake.
Good healthy food
Always crowded but worth it :)
Food court place inside Lesley University with good, fast Japanese curry. Not much seating and full of students, but good for a quick bite when in the area.
Super cheap eats and huge portions

Delicious food for a cheap price. If you are around the area, it is a great place to grab food for lunch or even dinner. A huge plus is that there is parking and does not cost an arm or a leg. Here's the breakdown:  Atmosphere: So I'm gonna go pretty lenient on this place, because it's technically in a tiny food court kind of thing. There are not a lot of seating, so you might have to wait for a seat and might have to even share a table with someone (it's really not that bad, trust me). You can also see the cooks making the food in the back...you can literally see them pounding on a beef patty to make the Hamburg.  Food: The curry awesome..although I would probably prefer Go! Go! Curry! in H-Mart. The one thing I come here for is the salad that comes with the entree. It is a pretty basic sauce, but I LOVE it! I normally don't even like salad, but damn I always keep coming back for it. Also, if you like green tea (not jasmine) I would recommend their green tea smoothie. It is the BOMB.  Service: What can I say? Their literally two steps away from you. Whatever you need you can just raise your pinky and they will be there to help you.  Overall: Cheap but delicious food. Definitely recommended for lunch and even dinner. Try the hamburg or the curry katsu.
Very lovely place for hamburg, only if there was more space. The prices are good, quality is good, nice atmosphere, and friendly service.
Although they changed ownership/management a few years ago, the food and fast service are still excellent.
The gyu don was excellent.

Located at a Japanese food court at Porter Square. Limited seating - only 2 or 3 tables with some seats at the counter. I've always avoided the rush, but there can be a line at times. Love the Tokyo hamburg set - comes with miso soup, salad, baked potato, and a beef hamburg covered in very tasty sauce. They also have dons, curry, and The portions are decent and filling. It is CASH ONLY so make sure you have enough cash, but if not, there are plenty of ATMs around the mall for you to withdraw some.

SO good! Japanese, home-cooked, amazing. Quick and cheap.
